+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0164x4j7QweP4EebuiUhktjt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Autopilot design decisions:**\n\n---\n\n**Q: Overall architecture - class-based manager vs. functional API?**\n→ Choosing: **Class-based `TaskQueue` manager**\n  Reasoning: Single object managing all named queues, lifecycle state (shutdown), middleware registries, and schedules. Easier to test in isolation and matches Bull/Celery mental model.\n\n---\n\n**Q: Task identity and state machine?**\n→ Choosing: **UUID v4 IDs, status enum: `pending | processing | completed | failed | cancelled | blocked`**\n  Reasoning: `blocked` is needed for dependency tracking (phase 7). All states must be in the core type from day one to avoid breaking changes.\n\n---\n\n**Q: Priority queue implementation?**\n→ Choosing: **Sorted array with binary insertion**\n  Reasoning: Simple, no external deps, correct FIFO tie-breaking. Max ~hundreds of tasks in memory. O(n) insert acceptable.\n\n---\n\n**Q: Scheduling / delayed tasks - clock mechanism?**\n→ Choosing: **Inject a `Date.now`-compatible clock function**, default to real `Date.now`. No real timers - consumers call `tick()`. This makes everything deterministic in tests.\n\n---\n\n**Q: Middleware - sync vs async?**\n→ Choosing: **Async middleware** (`async (task, next) => { ... }`) \n  Reasoning: Matches real-world patterns; allows async I/O in middleware. Compatible with phase 12 shutdown await.\n\n---\n\n**Q: Event system for progress (phase 9)?**\n→ Choosing: **Simple callback map** (`Map<taskId, Set<listener>>`) rather than EventEmitter\n  Reasoning: No external deps, deterministic, easy to unsubscribe. Returns unsubscribe function.\n\n---\n\nNow I'll write the design doc and proceed to implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":257,"cache_read_input_tokens":25216,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":257},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18fce2bb-6502-4a68-a464-ea2d12dfaf15","uuid":"141b0e3d-d514-4568-b850-2ad17197e7a2"}
+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0164x4j7QweP4EebuiUhktjt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018cN8er9cTnBSnaBCgtqKcn","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-task-queue-design.md","content":"# Task Queue System Design\n\n## Architecture\n\nSingle `TaskQueue` class exported from `src/index.ts` managing all state.\n\n## Core Data Model\n\n```ts\ntype TaskStatus = 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled' | 'blocked';\n\ninterface Task<P = unknown> {\n  id: string;                    // UUID v4\n  queueName: string;\n  payload: P;\n  status: TaskStatus;\n  priority: number;              // 1-10, default 5\n  createdAt: Date;\n  availableAt: Date;             // for delayed tasks\n  attempts: number;              // retry count\n  maxRetries: number;            // default 3\n  baseDelay: number;             // backoff base ms, default 1000\n  dependsOn: string[];           // task IDs\n  progress: number;              // 0-100\n  progressMessage?: string;\n  error?: Error;\n  lastFailedAt?: Date;\n}\n```\n\n## Internal Queue State (per named queue)\n\n- `pending: Task[]` — sorted by (priority ASC, availableAt ASC, createdAt ASC)\n- `processing: Set<string>` — task IDs currently processing\n- `dlq: Task[]` — dead letter queue\n- `maxConcurrency: number | null`\n- `middleware: MiddlewareFn[]`\n- `handler?: HandlerFn`\n- `schedules: Map<string, Schedule>`\n\n## Key Algorithms\n\n### dequeue(queueName)\n1. Check concurrency limit; return null if at cap\n2. Filter pending tasks where `availableAt <= now` AND `status !== blocked`\n3. Sort: priority ASC, availableAt ASC, createdAt ASC\n4. Return first; mark processing\n\n### complete(taskId)\n1. Mark completed\n2. Release concurrency slot\n3. Check if any blocked tasks now unblocked (all deps completed)\n4. Unblock them → pending\n\n### fail(taskId, error)\n1. Increment attempts\n2. If attempts < maxRetries: compute backoff delay, re-queue as pending with new availableAt\n3. Else: move to DLQ\n\n### Dependency detection (phase 7)\n- On add: validate all dep IDs exist\n- Detect cycles: DFS from new task following dependsOn edges; if new task reachable, cycle exists\n\n## Middleware (phase 11)\n```ts\ntype MiddlewareFn = (task: Task, next: () => Promise<void>) => Promise<void>;\n```\nComposed like Koa middleware.\n\n## Shutdown (phase 12)\n- `shuttingDown` flag blocks new task adds\n- Wait for `processing` sets to drain across all queues\n- Force-cancel after timeout\n\n## File Structure\n```\nsrc/\n  index.ts          — public API exports\n  TaskQueue.ts      — main class\n  types.ts          — all shared types\n  utils.ts          — UUID, sorting helpers\n  cron.ts           — cron expression parser/evaluator\n```\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":257,"cache_read_input_tokens":25216,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":257},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18fce2bb-6502-4a68-a464-ea2d12dfaf15","uuid":"2374df43-23d7-441b-9ce1-5a68f553e42f"}
