+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018psWeZQLQKus9FBr8uqtAH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018p47H2tXAgPzithYbTrXJZ","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-task-queue-implementation.md","content":"# Task Queue System Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system through 12 incremental phases, exported from `src/index.ts`.\n\n**Architecture:** Single `TaskQueue` class manages all named queues. Each queue has its own pending list (sorted by priority then FIFO), processing set, dead letter queue, middleware stack, and concurrency limit. A pluggable clock function (`() => number`) enables deterministic testing of delays and scheduling.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript 5.4, Vitest 2.x for tests, ESLint with `@typescript-eslint`, Node16 module resolution, no external runtime dependencies.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Project Scaffolding\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `src/utils.ts`\n- Create: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase01.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Create `src/types.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nexport type TaskStatus =\n  | 'pending'\n  | 'processing'\n  | 'completed'\n  | 'failed'\n  | 'cancelled'\n  | 'blocked';\n\nexport interface Task<P = unknown> {\n  id: string;\n  queueName: string;\n  payload: P;\n  status: TaskStatus;\n  priority: number;        // 1 (highest) to 10 (lowest), default 5\n  createdAt: Date;\n  availableAt: Date;       // for delayed tasks; equals createdAt for non-delayed\n  attempts: number;        // how many times attempted so far\n  maxRetries: number;      // default 3\n  baseDelay: number;       // backoff base in ms, default 1000\n  dependsOn: string[];     // task IDs that must complete first\n  progress: number;        // 0-100\n  progressMessage?: string;\n  error?: Error;\n}\n\nexport interface AddTaskOptions<P = unknown> {\n  payload: P;\n  priority?: number;       // 1-10\n  delay?: number;          // ms from now\n  availableAt?: Date;      // exact time\n  maxRetries?: number;\n  baseDelay?: number;\n  dependsOn?: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface QueueStats {\n  name: string;\n  pending: number;\n  processing: number;\n  dlq: number;\n  maxConcurrency: number | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create `src/utils.ts`**\n\n```typescript\n// Minimal UUID v4 using crypto (Node built-in)\nimport { randomUUID } from 'crypto';\n\nexport function generateId(): string {\n  return randomUUID();\n}\n\n/**\n * Compare two tasks for queue ordering:\n *   1. priority ASC (1 is highest)\n *   2. availableAt ASC\n *   3. createdAt ASC (FIFO)\n */\nexport function compareTasks(a: Task, b: Task): number {\n  if (a.priority !== b.priority) return a.priority - b.priority;\n  const avail = a.availableAt.getTime() - b.availableAt.getTime();\n  if (avail !== 0) return avail;\n  return a.createdAt.getTime() - b.createdAt.getTime();\n}\n```\n\nNote: add `import type { Task } from './types.js';` at the top.\n\n**Step 3: Create `src/TaskQueue.ts` (Phase 1 only)**\n\n```typescript\nimport { generateId, compareTasks } from './utils.js';\nimport type { Task, AddTaskOptions, QueueStats, TaskStatus } from './types.js';\n\ninterface QueueState {\n  pending: Task[];\n  processing: Set<string>;\n  dlq: Task[];\n  maxConcurrency: number | null;\n}\n\nexport class TaskQueue {\n  private queues = new Map<string, QueueState>();\n  private tasks = new Map<string, Task>(); // global id → task lookup\n  private clock: () => number;\n\n  constructor(clock: () => number = Date.now) {\n    this.clock = clock;\n  }\n\n  private getOrCreateQueue(name: string): QueueState {\n    if (!this.queues.has(name)) {\n      this.queues.set(name, {\n        pending: [],\n        processing: new Set(),\n        dlq: [],\n        maxConcurrency: null,\n      });\n    }\n    return this.queues.get(name)!;\n  }\n\n  add<P = unknown>(options: AddTaskOptions<P>, queueName = 'default'): Task<P> {\n    const now = new Date(this.clock());\n    const task: Task<P> = {\n      id: generateId(),\n      queueName,\n      payload: options.payload,\n      status: 'pending',\n      priority: options.priority ?? 5,\n      createdAt: now,\n      availableAt: now,\n      attempts: 0,\n      maxRetries: options.maxRetries ?? 3,\n      baseDelay: options.baseDelay ?? 1000,\n      dependsOn: [],\n      progress: 0,\n    };\n\n    if (task.priority < 1 || task.priority > 10) {\n      throw new Error(`Priority must be between 1 and 10, got ${task.priority}`);\n    }\n\n    const q = this.getOrCreateQueue(queueName);\n    this.tasks.set(task.id, task);\n    this.insertPending(q, task as Task);\n    return task;\n  }\n\n  private insertPending(q: QueueState, task: Task): void {\n    // Binary insertion to keep sorted order\n    let lo = 0, hi = q.pending.length;\n    while (lo < hi) {\n      const mid = (lo + hi) >>> 1;\n      if (compareTasks(q.pending[mid], task) <= 0) lo = mid + 1;\n      else hi = mid;\n    }\n    q.pending.splice(lo, 0, task);\n  }\n\n  dequeue(queueName = 'default'): Task | null {\n    const q = this.queues.get(queueName);\n    if (!q) return null;\n\n    if (q.maxConcurrency !== null && q.processing.size >= q.maxConcurrency) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    const now = this.clock();\n    const idx = q.pending.findIndex(\n      t => t.status === 'pending' && t.availableAt.getTime() <= now\n    );\n    if (idx === -1) return null;\n\n    const task = q.pending.splice(idx, 1)[0];\n    task.status = 'processing';\n    task.attempts += 1;\n    q.processing.add(task.id);\n    return task;\n  }\n\n  pendingCount(queueName = 'default'): number {\n    return this.queues.get(queueName)?.pending.filter(\n      t => t.status === 'pending'\n    ).length ?? 0;\n  }\n\n  getTask(id: string): Task | undefined {\n    return this.tasks.get(id);\n  }\n\n  listQueues(): string[] {\n    return Array.from(this.queues.keys());\n  }\n\n  stats(queueName = 'default'): QueueStats {\n    const q = this.queues.get(queueName);\n    return {\n      name: queueName,\n      pending: q?.pending.filter(t => t.status === 'pending').length ?? 0,\n      processing: q?.processing.size ?? 0,\n      dlq: q?.dlq.length ?? 0,\n      maxConcurrency: q?.maxConcurrency ?? null,\n    };\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Create `src/index.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nexport { TaskQueue } from './TaskQueue.js';\nexport type { Task, AddTaskOptions, QueueStats, TaskStatus } from './types.js';\n```\n\n**Step 5: Write `src/tests/phase01.test.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue', () => {\n  let q: TaskQueue;\n  beforeEach(() => { q = new TaskQueue(); });\n\n  it('returns a task with id, status=pending, createdAt', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'hello' });\n    expect(t.id).toBeTruthy();\n    expect(t.status).toBe('pending');\n    expect(t.createdAt).toBeInstanceOf(Date);\n  });\n\n  it('dequeue returns oldest task in processing state', () => {\n    q.add({ payload: 'first' });\n    q.add({ payload: 'second' });\n    const t = q.dequeue();\n    expect(t?.payload).toBe('first');\n    expect(t?.status).toBe('processing');\n  });\n\n  it('returns null when queue empty', () => {\n    expect(q.dequeue()).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('pendingCount reflects waiting tasks', () => {\n    q.add({ payload: 1 });\n    q.add({ payload: 2 });\n    expect(q.pendingCount()).toBe(2);\n    q.dequeue();\n    expect(q.pendingCount()).toBe(1);\n  });\n\n  it('each task has a unique id', () => {\n    const ids = new Set([1,2,3].map(() => q.add({ payload: null }).id));\n    expect(ids.size).toBe(3);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 6: Run tests**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\nExpected: all Phase 1 tests pass.\n\n**Step 7: Build and lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build && npm run lint\n```\nExpected: no errors.\n\n**Step 8: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 1 - basic FIFO queue with pending/processing status\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Phase 2 - Named Queues\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` (already supports named queues via `getOrCreateQueue`)\n- Create: `src/tests/phase02.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Verify named queues already work, write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase02.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 2: Named Queues', () => {\n  let q: TaskQueue;\n  beforeEach(() => { q = new TaskQueue(); });\n\n  it('tasks added to named queues are independent', () => {\n    q.add({ payload: 'a' }, 'alpha');\n    q.add({ payload: 'b' }, 'beta');\n    expect(q.dequeue('alpha')?.payload).toBe('a');\n    expect(q.dequeue('alpha')).toBeNull();\n    expect(q.dequeue('beta')?.payload).toBe('b');\n  });\n\n  it('omitting queue name uses \"default\"', () => {\n    q.add({ payload: 'default-task' });\n    expect(q.dequeue('default')?.payload).toBe('default-task');\n  });\n\n  it('listQueues returns all created queue names', () => {\n    q.add({ payload: 1 }, 'q1');\n    q.add({ payload: 2 }, 'q2');\n    q.add({ payload: 3 });\n    const names = q.listQueues();\n    expect(names).toContain('q1');\n    expect(names).toContain('q2');\n    expect(names).toContain('default');\n  });\n\n  it('dequeue from non-existent queue returns null', () => {\n    expect(q.dequeue('nonexistent')).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('each queue has independent pending count', () => {\n    q.add({ payload: 1 }, 'a');\n    q.add({ payload: 2 }, 'a');\n    q.add({ payload: 3 }, 'b');\n    expect(q.pendingCount('a')).toBe(2);\n    expect(q.pendingCount('b')).toBe(1);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\nExpected: all pass (implementation already supports this).\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 2 - named queues with independent state\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Phase 3 - Priority\n\n**Files:**\n- Verify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` (priority sorting already in compareTasks)\n- Create: `src/tests/phase03.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write priority tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase03.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 3: Priority', () => {\n  let q: TaskQueue;\n  beforeEach(() => { q = new TaskQueue(); });\n\n  it('higher priority (lower number) dequeues first', () => {\n    q.add({ payload: 'low', priority: 8 });\n    q.add({ payload: 'high', priority: 2 });\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('high');\n  });\n\n  it('same priority uses FIFO order', () => {\n    q.add({ payload: 'first', priority: 5 });\n    q.add({ payload: 'second', priority: 5 });\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('first');\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('second');\n  });\n\n  it('default priority is 5', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    expect(t.priority).toBe(5);\n  });\n\n  it('throws on priority < 1', () => {\n    expect(() => q.add({ payload: 'x', priority: 0 })).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('throws on priority > 10', () => {\n    expect(() => q.add({ payload: 'x', priority: 11 })).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('task object exposes priority', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', priority: 3 });\n    expect(t.priority).toBe(3);\n  });\n\n  it('priority works per-queue independently', () => {\n    q.add({ payload: 'a-low', priority: 9 }, 'a');\n    q.add({ payload: 'a-high', priority: 1 }, 'a');\n    q.add({ payload: 'b-only', priority: 5 }, 'b');\n    expect(q.dequeue('a')?.payload).toBe('a-high');\n    expect(q.dequeue('b')?.payload).toBe('b-only');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\nExpected: all pass.\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 3 - priority queue (1=highest, 10=lowest) with FIFO tie-breaking\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Phase 4 - Delayed Tasks\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` — handle `delay` and `availableAt` in `add()`, update `dequeue()` to filter by time\n- Create: `src/tests/phase04.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 3\n\n**Step 1: Update `add()` in TaskQueue.ts to handle delay/availableAt**\n\nIn the `add()` method, after creating the task, add:\n\n```typescript\nif (options.delay !== undefined) {\n  task.availableAt = new Date(this.clock() + options.delay);\n} else if (options.availableAt !== undefined) {\n  task.availableAt = options.availableAt;\n}\n// else availableAt remains = now (already set)\n```\n\n**Step 2: Verify dequeue already filters by availableAt**\n\nThe `dequeue` method already does:\n```typescript\nt.availableAt.getTime() <= now\n```\nThis is correct - no change needed.\n\n**Step 3: Add availableAt to AddTaskOptions type**\n\nAlready present in types.ts. Verify `delay?: number` and `availableAt?: Date` are there.\n\n**Step 4: Write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase04.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 4: Delayed Tasks', () => {\n  it('delayed task is not returned until delay passes', () => {\n    let now = 1000;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    q.add({ payload: 'delayed', delay: 500 });\n    expect(q.dequeue()).toBeNull();\n    now = 1600;\n    const t = q.dequeue();\n    expect(t?.payload).toBe('delayed');\n  });\n\n  it('non-delayed tasks are preferred over not-yet-available delayed', () => {\n    let now = 1000;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    q.add({ payload: 'delayed', delay: 500, priority: 1 });\n    q.add({ payload: 'immediate', priority: 5 });\n    // delayed has higher priority but not yet available\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('immediate');\n  });\n\n  it('availableAt can be set as a specific date', () => {\n    let now = 0;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    const future = new Date(5000);\n    q.add({ payload: 'scheduled', availableAt: future });\n    expect(q.dequeue()).toBeNull();\n    now = 5000;\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('scheduled');\n  });\n\n  it('task exposes availableAt', () => {\n    let now = 1000;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', delay: 300 });\n    expect(t.availableAt.getTime()).toBe(1300);\n  });\n\n  it('multiple delayed tasks available simultaneously ordered by priority then FIFO', () => {\n    let now = 0;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    q.add({ payload: 'p5-first', delay: 100, priority: 5 });\n    q.add({ payload: 'p3', delay: 100, priority: 3 });\n    q.add({ payload: 'p5-second', delay: 100, priority: 5 });\n    now = 200;\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('p3');\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('p5-first');\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('p5-second');\n  });\n\n  it('works with named queues', () => {\n    let now = 0;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    q.add({ payload: 'x', delay: 100 }, 'myqueue');\n    expect(q.dequeue('myqueue')).toBeNull();\n    now = 200;\n    expect(q.dequeue('myqueue')?.payload).toBe('x');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\nExpected: all pass.\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 4 - delayed tasks with configurable clock for testability\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Phase 5 - Retry with Backoff\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` — add `complete()` and `fail()` methods\n- Modify: `src/types.ts` — add `lastFailedAt?: Date` to Task interface\n- Create: `src/tests/phase05.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 4\n\n**Step 1: Add `lastFailedAt` to Task in types.ts**\n\n```typescript\nlastFailedAt?: Date;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add `complete()` method to TaskQueue**\n\n```typescript\ncomplete(taskId: string): void {\n  const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n  if (!task) throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} not found`);\n  if (task.status !== 'processing') throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} is not processing`);\n\n  task.status = 'completed';\n  const q = this.queues.get(task.queueName)!;\n  q.processing.delete(taskId);\n\n  // Unblock any tasks that depend on this one (phase 7 hook - safe to call now as no-op)\n  this.checkUnblocked(taskId);\n}\n\nprivate checkUnblocked(_completedId: string): void {\n  // Implemented in Phase 7; no-op for now\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Add `fail()` method to TaskQueue**\n\n```typescript\nfail(taskId: string, error?: Error): void {\n  const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n  if (!task) throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} not found`);\n  if (task.status !== 'processing') throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} is not processing`);\n\n  task.error = error;\n  task.lastFailedAt = new Date(this.clock());\n  const q = this.queues.get(task.queueName)!;\n  q.processing.delete(taskId);\n\n  if (task.attempts < task.maxRetries) {\n    // Exponential backoff: baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)\n    const backoff = task.baseDelay * Math.pow(2, task.attempts - 1);\n    task.availableAt = new Date(this.clock() + backoff);\n    task.status = 'pending';\n    this.insertPending(q, task);\n  } else {\n    task.status = 'failed';\n    q.dlq.push(task);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase05.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 5: Retry with Backoff', () => {\n  it('complete() marks task as completed', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.dequeue();\n    q.complete(t.id);\n    expect(t.status).toBe('completed');\n  });\n\n  it('fail() with retries remaining re-queues with backoff delay', () => {\n    let now = 0;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 3, baseDelay: 1000 });\n    q.dequeue(); // attempts=1\n    q.fail(t.id, new Error('oops'));\n    // backoff = 1000 * 2^(1-1) = 1000\n    expect(t.status).toBe('pending');\n    expect(t.availableAt.getTime()).toBe(1000);\n    expect(t.error?.message).toBe('oops');\n  });\n\n  it('fail() uses exponential backoff: baseDelay * 2^(attempt-1)', () => {\n    let now = 0;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 3, baseDelay: 100 });\n\n    q.dequeue(); q.fail(t.id); // attempt 1, backoff=100*2^0=100\n    expect(t.availableAt.getTime()).toBe(100);\n\n    now = 200; q.dequeue(); q.fail(t.id); // attempt 2, backoff=100*2^1=200\n    expect(t.availableAt.getTime()).toBe(400);\n\n    now = 500; q.dequeue(); q.fail(t.id); // attempt 3, backoff=100*2^2=400\n    expect(t.availableAt.getTime()).toBe(900);\n  });\n\n  it('fail() with no retries left marks as failed', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 1 });\n    q.dequeue();\n    q.fail(t.id, new Error('fatal'));\n    expect(t.status).toBe('failed');\n  });\n\n  it('retried task keeps original queue and priority', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', priority: 2 }, 'myqueue');\n    q.dequeue('myqueue');\n    q.fail(t.id);\n    expect(t.queueName).toBe('myqueue');\n    expect(t.priority).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('tracks attempt count', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 3 });\n    q.dequeue(); // attempts=1\n    q.fail(t.id);\n    q.dequeue(); // attempts=2\n    expect(t.attempts).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('maxRetries defaults to 3', () => {\n    const t = new TaskQueue().add({ payload: 'x' });\n    expect(t.maxRetries).toBe(3);\n  });\n\n  it('baseDelay defaults to 1000', () => {\n    const t = new TaskQueue().add({ payload: 'x' });\n    expect(t.baseDelay).toBe(1000);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\nExpected: all pass.\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 5 - retry with exponential backoff on failure\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Phase 6 - Dead Letter Queue\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` — add `getDLQ()`, `requeueFromDLQ()`, `clearDLQ()` methods\n- Modify: `src/types.ts` — add DLQ-related types\n- Create: `src/tests/phase06.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 5\n\n**Step 1: Note that fail() already moves to dlq after maxRetries exhausted**\n\nThe `fail()` method in Phase 5 already does `q.dlq.push(task)`. This is the DLQ behavior.\n\n**Step 2: Add DLQ management methods to TaskQueue**\n\n```typescript\ngetDLQ(queueName = 'default'): Task[] {\n  return [...(this.queues.get(queueName)?.dlq ?? [])];\n}\n\nrequeueFromDLQ(taskId: string): void {\n  const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n  if (!task) throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} not found`);\n\n  const q = this.queues.get(task.queueName);\n  if (!q) throw new Error(`Queue ${task.queueName} not found`);\n\n  const idx = q.dlq.findIndex(t => t.id === taskId);\n  if (idx === -1) throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} not in dead letter queue`);\n\n  q.dlq.splice(idx, 1);\n  task.status = 'pending';\n  task.attempts = 0;\n  task.availableAt = new Date(this.clock());\n  task.error = undefined;\n  this.insertPending(q, task);\n}\n\nclearDLQ(queueName = 'default'): void {\n  const q = this.queues.get(queueName);\n  if (q) q.dlq = [];\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase06.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue', () => {\n  function exhaustRetries(q: TaskQueue, taskId: string, maxRetries: number) {\n    for (let i = 0; i < maxRetries; i++) {\n      q.dequeue();\n      q.fail(taskId, new Error(`fail-${i}`));\n    }\n  }\n\n  it('failed task after maxRetries goes to DLQ', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 1 });\n    exhaustRetries(q, t.id, 1);\n    expect(q.getDLQ()).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(q.getDLQ()[0].id).toBe(t.id);\n  });\n\n  it('DLQ tasks retain error info', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 1 });\n    q.dequeue();\n    q.fail(t.id, new Error('terminal'));\n    const dlq = q.getDLQ();\n    expect(dlq[0].error?.message).toBe('terminal');\n  });\n\n  it('DLQ tasks retain attempt count', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 2 });\n    exhaustRetries(q, t.id, 2);\n    expect(q.getDLQ()[0].attempts).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('requeueFromDLQ moves task back to pending with reset attempts', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 1 });\n    exhaustRetries(q, t.id, 1);\n    q.requeueFromDLQ(t.id);\n    expect(t.status).toBe('pending');\n    expect(t.attempts).toBe(0);\n    expect(q.getDLQ()).toHaveLength(0);\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.id).toBe(t.id);\n  });\n\n  it('clearDLQ empties dead letter queue', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 1 });\n    exhaustRetries(q, t.id, 1);\n    q.clearDLQ();\n    expect(q.getDLQ()).toHaveLength(0);\n  });\n\n  it('each named queue has independent DLQ', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t1 = q.add({ payload: 'a', maxRetries: 1 }, 'qa');\n    const t2 = q.add({ payload: 'b', maxRetries: 1 }, 'qb');\n    exhaustRetries(q, t1.id, 1);\n    exhaustRetries(q, t2.id, 1);\n    expect(q.getDLQ('qa')).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(q.getDLQ('qb')).toHaveLength(1);\n    q.clearDLQ('qa');\n    expect(q.getDLQ('qa')).toHaveLength(0);\n    expect(q.getDLQ('qb')).toHaveLength(1);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 6 - dead letter queue with requeue and clear\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Phase 7 - Task Dependencies\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` — validate deps in `add()`, implement `checkUnblocked()`, add `getDependencyStatus()`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase07.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 6\n\n**Step 1: Update `add()` to handle dependencies**\n\nIn `add()`, after priority validation, add:\n\n```typescript\n// Validate dependencies\nconst deps = options.dependsOn ?? [];\nfor (const depId of deps) {\n  if (!this.tasks.has(depId)) {\n    throw new Error(`Dependency task ${depId} does not exist`);\n  }\n}\ntask.dependsOn = deps;\n\n// Check for circular dependencies\nif (deps.length > 0 && this.hasCycle(task.id, deps)) {\n  throw new Error(`Circular dependency detected for task ${task.id}`);\n}\n\n// Check if any deps are not yet completed → block the task\nconst hasUnresolvedDeps = deps.some(depId => {\n  const dep = this.tasks.get(depId)!;\n  return dep.status !== 'completed';\n});\nif (hasUnresolvedDeps) {\n  task.status = 'blocked';\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Implement cycle detection**\n\n```typescript\nprivate hasCycle(newTaskId: string, deps: string[]): boolean {\n  // Check if newTaskId is reachable from any dep (would create cycle)\n  // Since newTaskId isn't in tasks yet, we check if any existing task\n  // in the dep graph eventually depends on newTaskId — but newTaskId\n  // is brand new so the check is: can we reach newTaskId through deps?\n  // Answer: no, since newTaskId isn't in the graph yet.\n  // The real cycle is: does any dep transitively depend on something\n  // that will depend on newTaskId? Since we haven't added it yet,\n  // the only cycle risk is if a dep's own dep chain includes the *same*\n  // task twice. Actually for a NEW task, cycle = if the new task is\n  // in its own reachable dep set. Since it's new, this is always false.\n  // BUT: we need to detect: does any dep depend (transitively) on newTaskId?\n  // Since newTaskId doesn't exist in tasks yet, that's impossible.\n  //\n  // Correction: cycles can only form if user reuses IDs (not possible with UUID)\n  // OR if they create A→B and then B→A. B→A means when adding B, A already exists.\n  // So: check if newTaskId appears in the transitive deps of any dep.\n  // Since newTaskId is new, this is impossible. Cycles happen when:\n  //   addTask(depId=[existingId]) where existingId transitively depends on newTaskId\n  //   But newTaskId doesn't exist yet.\n  //\n  // THEREFORE: cycles are impossible for newly-created tasks.\n  // The spec says detect direct or indirect cycles. With UUIDs for new tasks,\n  // the only way to get a cycle is if we allow tasks to be updated to add deps.\n  // We don't support that. So cycle detection is: no-op (always false) for new tasks.\n  // BUT to be safe and spec-compliant, implement DFS anyway:\n\n  const visited = new Set<string>();\n  const stack = [...deps];\n  while (stack.length > 0) {\n    const cur = stack.pop()!;\n    if (cur === newTaskId) return true; // found cycle\n    if (visited.has(cur)) continue;\n    visited.add(cur);\n    const curTask = this.tasks.get(cur);\n    if (curTask) {\n      stack.push(...curTask.dependsOn);\n    }\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Implement `checkUnblocked()`**\n\nReplace the no-op stub:\n\n```typescript\nprivate checkUnblocked(completedId: string): void {\n  for (const [, task] of this.tasks) {\n    if (task.status !== 'blocked') continue;\n    if (!task.dependsOn.includes(completedId)) continue;\n\n    // Check if ALL deps are now completed\n    const allDone = task.dependsOn.every(depId => {\n      const dep = this.tasks.get(depId);\n      return dep?.status === 'completed';\n    });\n\n    if (allDone) {\n      task.status = 'pending';\n      const q = this.getOrCreateQueue(task.queueName);\n      this.insertPending(q, task);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Add `getDependencyStatus()`**\n\n```typescript\ngetDependencyStatus(taskId: string): {\n  resolved: string[];\n  pending: string[];\n} {\n  const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n  if (!task) throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} not found`);\n\n  const resolved: string[] = [];\n  const pending: string[] = [];\n\n  for (const depId of task.dependsOn) {\n    const dep = this.tasks.get(depId);\n    if (dep?.status === 'completed') {\n      resolved.push(depId);\n    } else {\n      pending.push(depId);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { resolved, pending };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 5: Update `dequeue()` to skip blocked tasks**\n\nThe `dequeue` method already filters `t.status === 'pending'`. Since blocked tasks have `status === 'blocked'`, they're automatically excluded. No change needed.\n\n**Step 6: Write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase07.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 7: Task Dependencies', () => {\n  let q: TaskQueue;\n  beforeEach(() => { q = new TaskQueue(); });\n\n  it('task with unresolved deps is blocked', () => {\n    const dep = q.add({ payload: 'dep' });\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'child', dependsOn: [dep.id] });\n    expect(t.status).toBe('blocked');\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.id).toBe(dep.id); // only dep available\n    expect(q.dequeue()).toBeNull(); // child still blocked\n  });\n\n  it('completing a dep unblocks the child', () => {\n    const dep = q.add({ payload: 'dep' });\n    const child = q.add({ payload: 'child', dependsOn: [dep.id] });\n    q.dequeue();\n    q.complete(dep.id);\n    expect(child.status).toBe('pending');\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.id).toBe(child.id);\n  });\n\n  it('child stays blocked until ALL deps complete', () => {\n    const d1 = q.add({ payload: 'd1' });\n    const d2 = q.add({ payload: 'd2' });\n    const child = q.add({ payload: 'child', dependsOn: [d1.id, d2.id] });\n    q.dequeue(); q.complete(d1.id);\n    expect(child.status).toBe('blocked');\n    q.dequeue(); q.complete(d2.id);\n    expect(child.status).toBe('pending');\n  });\n\n  it('failed dep does NOT auto-fail child - child stays blocked', () => {\n    const dep = q.add({ payload: 'dep' });\n    const child = q.add({ payload: 'child', dependsOn: [dep.id] });\n    q.dequeue();\n    q.fail(dep.id, new Error('oops'));\n    // dep will retry - child still blocked\n    expect(child.status).toBe('blocked');\n  });\n\n  it('adding dep on non-existent task throws', () => {\n    expect(() => q.add({ payload: 'x', dependsOn: ['nonexistent-id'] })).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('circular dependency detection', () => {\n    const a = q.add({ payload: 'a' });\n    const b = q.add({ payload: 'b', dependsOn: [a.id] });\n    expect(() => q.add({ payload: 'c', dependsOn: [b.id], })).not.toThrow();\n    // try to make a depend on something that transitively depends on itself\n    // (can't really do this with new tasks - test direct: a→b→a not possible since a already exists)\n    // Instead test: can't create task that already has a cycle in dep chain\n    const x = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    const y = q.add({ payload: 'y', dependsOn: [x.id] });\n    // Now try adding z with dependsOn [y.id] — that's fine\n    expect(() => q.add({ payload: 'z', dependsOn: [y.id] })).not.toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('getDependencyStatus shows resolved and pending deps', () => {\n    const d1 = q.add({ payload: 'd1' });\n    const d2 = q.add({ payload: 'd2' });\n    const child = q.add({ payload: 'child', dependsOn: [d1.id, d2.id] });\n    q.dequeue(); q.complete(d1.id);\n    const status = q.getDependencyStatus(child.id);\n    expect(status.resolved).toContain(d1.id);\n    expect(status.pending).toContain(d2.id);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 7: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\n\n**Step 8: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 7 - task dependencies with cycle detection and auto-unblocking\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Phase 8 - Concurrency Control\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` — add `setConcurrency()`, `getConcurrencyInfo()`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase08.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 7\n\n**Step 1: Note that concurrency limit already respected in `dequeue()`**\n\nThe `dequeue()` already checks:\n```typescript\nif (q.maxConcurrency !== null && q.processing.size >= q.maxConcurrency) {\n  return null;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add setter/getter for concurrency**\n\n```typescript\nsetConcurrency(queueName: string, limit: number | null): void {\n  const q = this.getOrCreateQueue(queueName);\n  q.maxConcurrency = limit;\n}\n\ngetConcurrencyInfo(queueName = 'default'): {\n  limit: number | null;\n  active: number;\n} {\n  const q = this.queues.get(queueName);\n  return {\n    limit: q?.maxConcurrency ?? null,\n    active: q?.processing.size ?? 0,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Ensure complete/fail decrements processing (already done)**\n\nThe `processing` Set already has `delete()` called in `complete()` and `fail()`.\n\n**Step 4: Write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase08.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 8: Concurrency Control', () => {\n  it('default is no concurrency limit', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) q.add({ payload: i });\n    for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) expect(q.dequeue()).not.toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('concurrency limit blocks dequeue when at capacity', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    q.setConcurrency('default', 2);\n    q.add({ payload: 1 }); q.add({ payload: 2 }); q.add({ payload: 3 });\n    q.dequeue(); q.dequeue();\n    expect(q.dequeue()).toBeNull(); // at capacity\n  });\n\n  it('completing a task frees a slot', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    q.setConcurrency('default', 1);\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.add({ payload: 'y' });\n    q.dequeue();\n    expect(q.dequeue()).toBeNull();\n    q.complete(t.id);\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('y');\n  });\n\n  it('failing a task frees a slot', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    q.setConcurrency('default', 1);\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 0 });\n    q.add({ payload: 'y' });\n    q.dequeue();\n    q.fail(t.id);\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('y');\n  });\n\n  it('getConcurrencyInfo returns limit and active count', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    q.setConcurrency('default', 3);\n    q.add({ payload: 1 }); q.add({ payload: 2 });\n    q.dequeue(); q.dequeue();\n    const info = q.getConcurrencyInfo();\n    expect(info.limit).toBe(3);\n    expect(info.active).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('highest-priority task is chosen when concurrency allows', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    q.setConcurrency('default', 1);\n    q.add({ payload: 'low', priority: 9 });\n    q.add({ payload: 'high', priority: 1 });\n    expect(q.dequeue()?.payload).toBe('high');\n  });\n\n  it('setConcurrency(null) removes limit', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    q.setConcurrency('default', 1);\n    q.add({ payload: 1 }); q.add({ payload: 2 });\n    q.dequeue();\n    expect(q.dequeue()).toBeNull();\n    q.setConcurrency('default', null);\n    expect(q.dequeue()).not.toBeNull();\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 8 - concurrency control per queue\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Phase 9 - Progress and Cancellation\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` — add `reportProgress()`, `onProgress()`, `cancel()`\n- Modify: `src/types.ts` — add `ProgressListener` type\n- Create: `src/tests/phase09.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 8\n\n**Step 1: Add types**\n\n```typescript\n// In types.ts:\nexport type ProgressListener = (progress: number, message?: string) => void;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add progress listener storage to TaskQueue**\n\nIn class:\n```typescript\nprivate progressListeners = new Map<string, Set<ProgressListener>>();\n```\n\n**Step 3: Implement `reportProgress()`**\n\n```typescript\nreportProgress(taskId: string, progress: number, message?: string): void {\n  const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n  if (!task) throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} not found`);\n  if (task.status !== 'processing') throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} is not processing`);\n  if (progress < 0 || progress > 100) throw new Error('Progress must be 0-100');\n\n  task.progress = progress;\n  task.progressMessage = message;\n\n  const listeners = this.progressListeners.get(taskId);\n  if (listeners) {\n    for (const listener of listeners) {\n      listener(progress, message);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Implement `onProgress()` returning unsubscribe**\n\n```typescript\nonProgress(taskId: string, listener: ProgressListener): () => void {\n  if (!this.progressListeners.has(taskId)) {\n    this.progressListeners.set(taskId, new Set());\n  }\n  const listeners = this.progressListeners.get(taskId)!;\n  listeners.add(listener);\n\n  return () => {\n    listeners.delete(listener);\n    if (listeners.size === 0) {\n      this.progressListeners.delete(taskId);\n    }\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 5: Implement `cancel()`**\n\n```typescript\ncancel(taskId: string): void {\n  const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n  if (!task) throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} not found`);\n\n  if (task.status !== 'pending' && task.status !== 'processing' && task.status !== 'blocked') {\n    throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} cannot be cancelled in status: ${task.status}`);\n  }\n\n  const q = this.queues.get(task.queueName);\n\n  if (task.status === 'pending' || task.status === 'blocked') {\n    // Remove from pending list\n    if (q) {\n      const idx = q.pending.findIndex(t => t.id === taskId);\n      if (idx !== -1) q.pending.splice(idx, 1);\n    }\n  } else if (task.status === 'processing') {\n    if (q) q.processing.delete(taskId);\n  }\n\n  task.status = 'cancelled';\n  // Clean up listeners\n  this.progressListeners.delete(taskId);\n}\n```\n\n**Step 6: Write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase09.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 9: Progress and Cancellation', () => {\n  let q: TaskQueue;\n  beforeEach(() => { q = new TaskQueue(); });\n\n  it('reportProgress updates task progress', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.dequeue();\n    q.reportProgress(t.id, 50, 'halfway');\n    expect(t.progress).toBe(50);\n    expect(t.progressMessage).toBe('halfway');\n  });\n\n  it('onProgress listener is called on progress update', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.dequeue();\n    const updates: number[] = [];\n    q.onProgress(t.id, (p) => updates.push(p));\n    q.reportProgress(t.id, 25);\n    q.reportProgress(t.id, 75);\n    expect(updates).toEqual([25, 75]);\n  });\n\n  it('unsubscribe stops future notifications', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.dequeue();\n    const updates: number[] = [];\n    const unsub = q.onProgress(t.id, (p) => updates.push(p));\n    q.reportProgress(t.id, 10);\n    unsub();\n    q.reportProgress(t.id, 20);\n    expect(updates).toEqual([10]);\n  });\n\n  it('cancel pending task removes from queue', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.cancel(t.id);\n    expect(t.status).toBe('cancelled');\n    expect(q.dequeue()).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('cancel processing task updates status', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.dequeue();\n    q.cancel(t.id);\n    expect(t.status).toBe('cancelled');\n  });\n\n  it('cancelled task is never retried', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 3 });\n    q.dequeue();\n    q.cancel(t.id);\n    expect(q.dequeue()).toBeNull();\n    expect(t.status).toBe('cancelled');\n  });\n\n  it('reportProgress throws on invalid range', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.dequeue();\n    expect(() => q.reportProgress(t.id, 101)).toThrow();\n    expect(() => q.reportProgress(t.id, -1)).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('pendingCount does not include cancelled tasks', () => {\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.cancel(t.id);\n    expect(q.pendingCount()).toBe(0);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 7: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\n\n**Step 8: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 9 - progress tracking with listeners and task cancellation\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Phase 10 - Recurring Tasks\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/cron.ts`\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` — add schedule management, `tick()`\n- Modify: `src/types.ts` — add Schedule type\n- Create: `src/tests/phase10.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 9\n\n**Step 1: Add Schedule type to types.ts**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Schedule {\n  id: string;\n  queueName: string;\n  cronExpression: string;\n  payload: unknown;\n  lastRun?: Date;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create `src/cron.ts`**\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Parses and evaluates a subset of cron expressions:\n *   \"* /N * * * *\"  — every N minutes (no space between * and /)\n *   \"0 * * * *\"     — every hour at minute 0\n *   \"0 0 * * *\"     — every day at midnight\n */\nexport function isDue(expression: string, lastRun: Date | undefined, now: Date): boolean {\n  const parts = expression.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  if (parts.length !== 5) throw new Error(`Invalid cron expression: ${expression}`);\n\n  const [minute, hour, dom, month, dow] = parts;\n\n  // Parse \"*/N\" pattern\n  const everyNMatch = minute.match(/^\\*\\/(\\d+)$/);\n\n  if (everyNMatch && hour === '*' && dom === '*' && month === '*' && dow === '*') {\n    // \"*/N * * * *\" — every N minutes\n    const n = parseInt(everyNMatch[1], 10);\n    if (n <= 0) throw new Error(`Invalid cron interval: ${n}`);\n    if (!lastRun) return true; // never run\n    const msSince = now.getTime() - lastRun.getTime();\n    return msSince >= n * 60 * 1000;\n  }\n\n  if (minute === '0' && hour === '*' && dom === '*' && month === '*' && dow === '*') {\n    // \"0 * * * *\" — every hour on the hour\n    if (!lastRun) return now.getMinutes() === 0;\n    const msSince = now.getTime() - lastRun.getTime();\n    return msSince >= 60 * 60 * 1000;\n  }\n\n  if (minute === '0' && hour === '0' && dom === '*' && month === '*' && dow === '*') {\n    // \"0 0 * * *\" — every day at midnight\n    if (!lastRun) return now.getHours() === 0 && now.getMinutes() === 0;\n    const msSince = now.getTime() - lastRun.getTime();\n    return msSince >= 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000;\n  }\n\n  throw new Error(`Unsupported cron expression: ${expression}`);\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Add schedule storage and methods to TaskQueue**\n\n```typescript\nprivate schedules = new Map<string, Schedule>();\n\naddSchedule(id: string, options: {\n  queueName?: string;\n  cronExpression: string;\n  payload: unknown;\n}): Schedule {\n  const schedule: Schedule = {\n    id,\n    queueName: options.queueName ?? 'default',\n    cronExpression: options.cronExpression,\n    payload: options.payload,\n  };\n  this.schedules.set(id, schedule);\n  return schedule;\n}\n\nremoveSchedule(id: string): void {\n  if (!this.schedules.has(id)) throw new Error(`Schedule ${id} not found`);\n  this.schedules.delete(id);\n}\n\nlistSchedules(): Schedule[] {\n  return Array.from(this.schedules.values());\n}\n\ntick(): Task[] {\n  const now = new Date(this.clock());\n  const enqueued: Task[] = [];\n\n  for (const schedule of this.schedules.values()) {\n    if (isDue(schedule.cronExpression, schedule.lastRun, now)) {\n      schedule.lastRun = now;\n      const task = this.add({ payload: schedule.payload }, schedule.queueName);\n      enqueued.push(task);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return enqueued;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase10.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 10: Recurring Tasks', () => {\n  it('tick() enqueues tasks for due schedules', () => {\n    let now = 0;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    q.addSchedule('every-minute', {\n      cronExpression: '*/1 * * * *',\n      payload: { type: 'heartbeat' },\n    });\n    now = 61 * 1000; // 1 minute 1 second later\n    const tasks = q.tick();\n    expect(tasks).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(tasks[0].payload).toEqual({ type: 'heartbeat' });\n  });\n\n  it('tick() does not enqueue if not enough time has passed', () => {\n    let now = 0;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    q.addSchedule('every-5min', {\n      cronExpression: '*/5 * * * *',\n      payload: 'x',\n    });\n    now = 4 * 60 * 1000; // only 4 minutes\n    expect(q.tick()).toHaveLength(0);\n  });\n\n  it('tick() enqueues on first call (never run before)', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => 0);\n    q.addSchedule('hourly', {\n      cronExpression: '0 * * * *',\n      payload: 'y',\n    });\n    // First tick with now=0, hour:min=0:0 — should enqueue\n    const tasks = q.tick();\n    expect(tasks.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n  });\n\n  it('removeSchedule stops future enqueuing', () => {\n    let now = 0;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    q.addSchedule('s1', { cronExpression: '*/1 * * * *', payload: null });\n    q.removeSchedule('s1');\n    now = 120 * 1000;\n    expect(q.tick()).toHaveLength(0);\n  });\n\n  it('listSchedules returns all active schedules', () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    q.addSchedule('a', { cronExpression: '*/5 * * * *', payload: 1 });\n    q.addSchedule('b', { cronExpression: '0 * * * *', payload: 2 });\n    const schedules = q.listSchedules();\n    expect(schedules.map(s => s.id)).toContain('a');\n    expect(schedules.map(s => s.id)).toContain('b');\n  });\n\n  it('recurring tasks are regular tasks subject to queue rules', () => {\n    let now = 0;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    q.addSchedule('s', {\n      cronExpression: '*/1 * * * *',\n      payload: 'recurring',\n      queueName: 'jobs',\n    });\n    now = 61 * 1000;\n    q.tick();\n    expect(q.dequeue('jobs')?.payload).toBe('recurring');\n  });\n\n  it('multiple schedules evaluated independently', () => {\n    let now = 0;\n    const q = new TaskQueue(() => now);\n    q.addSchedule('fast', { cronExpression: '*/1 * * * *', payload: 'f' });\n    q.addSchedule('slow', { cronExpression: '*/5 * * * *', payload: 's' });\n    now = 61 * 1000; // 1 min — only fast is due\n    // fast has never run, slow has never run\n    const tasks = q.tick();\n    // both should fire on first tick (never run before = due)\n    expect(tasks.length).toBe(2);\n    // after tick, advance only 1 more minute\n    now = 121 * 1000;\n    const tasks2 = q.tick();\n    // fast fires again, slow doesn't (only 1 min since last)\n    expect(tasks2.map(t => t.payload)).toContain('f');\n    expect(tasks2.map(t => t.payload)).not.toContain('s');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 10 - recurring tasks with cron expressions and tick mechanism\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 11: Phase 11 - Middleware Pipeline\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` — add `use()`, `registerHandler()`, `process()`\n- Modify: `src/types.ts` — add MiddlewareFn, HandlerFn types\n- Create: `src/tests/phase11.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 10\n\n**Step 1: Add middleware types to types.ts**\n\n```typescript\nexport type MiddlewareFn<P = unknown> = (\n  task: Task<P>,\n  next: () => Promise<void>\n) => Promise<void>;\n\nexport type HandlerFn<P = unknown> = (task: Task<P>) => Promise<void>;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add middleware storage to TaskQueue**\n\n```typescript\nprivate middlewares = new Map<string, MiddlewareFn[]>();\nprivate handlers = new Map<string, HandlerFn>();\n```\n\n**Step 3: Add `use()` and `registerHandler()`**\n\n```typescript\nuse(queueName: string, middleware: MiddlewareFn): void {\n  if (!this.middlewares.has(queueName)) {\n    this.middlewares.set(queueName, []);\n  }\n  this.middlewares.get(queueName)!.push(middleware);\n}\n\nregisterHandler(queueName: string, handler: HandlerFn): void {\n  this.handlers.set(queueName, handler);\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Add `process()` that dequeues and runs middleware + handler**\n\n```typescript\nasync process(queueName = 'default'): Promise<boolean> {\n  const task = this.dequeue(queueName);\n  if (!task) return false;\n\n  const middlewares = this.middlewares.get(queueName) ?? [];\n  const handler = this.handlers.get(queueName);\n\n  // Build middleware chain\n  const chain = [...middlewares];\n\n  let index = 0;\n  const next = async (): Promise<void> => {\n    if (index < chain.length) {\n      const mw = chain[index++];\n      await mw(task, next);\n    } else if (handler) {\n      await handler(task);\n    }\n  };\n\n  try {\n    await next();\n    // If handler completed normally, mark complete\n    if (task.status === 'processing') {\n      this.complete(task.id);\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    if (task.status === 'processing') {\n      this.fail(task.id, err instanceof Error ? err : new Error(String(err)));\n    }\n  }\n\n  return true;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 5: Write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase11.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline', () => {\n  let q: TaskQueue;\n  beforeEach(() => { q = new TaskQueue(); });\n\n  it('middleware runs before handler', async () => {\n    const order: string[] = [];\n    q.use('default', async (task, next) => {\n      order.push('mw1');\n      await next();\n    });\n    q.registerHandler('default', async () => { order.push('handler'); });\n    q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    await q.process();\n    expect(order).toEqual(['mw1', 'handler']);\n  });\n\n  it('multiple middleware run in registration order', async () => {\n    const order: string[] = [];\n    q.use('default', async (task, next) => { order.push('mw1'); await next(); });\n    q.use('default', async (task, next) => { order.push('mw2'); await next(); });\n    q.registerHandler('default', async () => { order.push('handler'); });\n    q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    await q.process();\n    expect(order).toEqual(['mw1', 'mw2', 'handler']);\n  });\n\n  it('middleware that does not call next skips remaining pipeline', async () => {\n    const order: string[] = [];\n    q.use('default', async (_task, _next) => { order.push('blocker'); }); // no next()\n    q.registerHandler('default', async () => { order.push('handler'); });\n    q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    await q.process();\n    expect(order).toEqual(['blocker']);\n    expect(order).not.toContain('handler');\n  });\n\n  it('middleware can modify task payload', async () => {\n    let seenPayload: unknown;\n    q.use('default', async (task, next) => {\n      (task as { payload: unknown }).payload = 'modified';\n      await next();\n    });\n    q.registerHandler('default', async (task) => { seenPayload = task.payload; });\n    q.add({ payload: 'original' });\n    await q.process();\n    expect(seenPayload).toBe('modified');\n  });\n\n  it('middleware throwing marks task as failed', async () => {\n    q.use('default', async () => { throw new Error('mw error'); });\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x', maxRetries: 0 });\n    await q.process();\n    // After maxRetries=0, goes to DLQ\n    const dlq = q.getDLQ();\n    expect(dlq.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n  });\n\n  it('each queue has independent middleware stack', async () => {\n    const aOrder: string[] = [];\n    const bOrder: string[] = [];\n    q.use('a', async (task, next) => { aOrder.push('a-mw'); await next(); });\n    q.use('b', async (task, next) => { bOrder.push('b-mw'); await next(); });\n    q.add({ payload: 1 }, 'a');\n    q.add({ payload: 2 }, 'b');\n    await q.process('a');\n    await q.process('b');\n    expect(aOrder).toEqual(['a-mw']);\n    expect(bOrder).toEqual(['b-mw']);\n  });\n\n  it('process() returns false when queue empty', async () => {\n    expect(await q.process()).toBe(false);\n  });\n\n  it('process() returns true when task processed', async () => {\n    q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    expect(await q.process()).toBe(true);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 6: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\n\n**Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 11 - async middleware pipeline per queue\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 12: Phase 12 - Graceful Shutdown\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts` — add `shutdown()`, `onShutdown()`, `isShuttingDown()`\n- Modify: `src/types.ts` — add ShutdownResult type\n- Create: `src/tests/phase12.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 11\n\n**Step 1: Add ShutdownResult to types.ts**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface ShutdownResult {\n  completed: number;\n  forceCancelled: number;\n  durationMs: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add shutdown state to TaskQueue**\n\n```typescript\nprivate _shuttingDown = false;\nprivate _shutdownResult: ShutdownResult | null = null;\nprivate _shutdownCallbacks: Array<() => void | Promise<void>> = [];\n```\n\n**Step 3: Update `add()` to reject after shutdown**\n\nAt the beginning of `add()`:\n```typescript\nif (this._shuttingDown) {\n  throw new Error('TaskQueue is shutting down; no new tasks accepted');\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Implement `isShuttingDown()` and `onShutdown()`**\n\n```typescript\nisShuttingDown(): boolean {\n  return this._shuttingDown;\n}\n\nonShutdown(callback: () => void | Promise<void>): void {\n  this._shutdownCallbacks.push(callback);\n}\n```\n\n**Step 5: Implement `shutdown()`**\n\n```typescript\nasync shutdown(timeoutMs = 30000): Promise<ShutdownResult> {\n  // Idempotent - return same result if already shut down\n  if (this._shutdownResult) return this._shutdownResult;\n  if (this._shuttingDown) {\n    // Wait for ongoing shutdown\n    return new Promise(resolve => {\n      const check = setInterval(() => {\n        if (this._shutdownResult) {\n          clearInterval(check);\n          resolve(this._shutdownResult);\n        }\n      }, 10);\n    });\n  }\n\n  this._shuttingDown = true;\n  const startTime = this.clock();\n\n  // Run shutdown callbacks\n  for (const cb of this._shutdownCallbacks) {\n    await cb();\n  }\n\n  // Count initially processing tasks\n  let processingIds: string[] = [];\n  for (const [, q] of this.queues) {\n    processingIds.push(...q.processing);\n  }\n\n  // If no processing tasks, done immediately\n  if (processingIds.length === 0) {\n    const result: ShutdownResult = {\n      completed: 0,\n      forceCancelled: 0,\n      durationMs: this.clock() - startTime,\n    };\n    this._shutdownResult = result;\n    return result;\n  }\n\n  // Wait for processing tasks to drain\n  const deadline = startTime + timeoutMs;\n\n  return new Promise<ShutdownResult>(resolve => {\n    const checkDone = () => {\n      const nowMs = this.clock();\n\n      // Collect still-processing task IDs\n      const stillProcessing: string[] = [];\n      for (const [, q] of this.queues) {\n        stillProcessing.push(...q.processing);\n      }\n\n      if (stillProcessing.length === 0) {\n        // All done naturally\n        const result: ShutdownResult = {\n          completed: processingIds.length, // all were completed\n          forceCancelled: 0,\n          durationMs: nowMs - startTime,\n        };\n        this._shutdownResult = result;\n        resolve(result);\n        return;\n      }\n\n      if (nowMs >= deadline) {\n        // Timeout — force cancel remaining\n        let forceCancelled = 0;\n        for (const id of stillProcessing) {\n          const task = this.tasks.get(id);\n          if (task && task.status === 'processing') {\n            const q = this.queues.get(task.queueName)!;\n            q.processing.delete(id);\n            task.status = 'cancelled';\n            forceCancelled++;\n          }\n        }\n        const completed = processingIds.length - forceCancelled;\n        const result: ShutdownResult = {\n          completed,\n          forceCancelled,\n          durationMs: nowMs - startTime,\n        };\n        this._shutdownResult = result;\n        resolve(result);\n        return;\n      }\n\n      setTimeout(checkDone, 10);\n    };\n\n    checkDone();\n  });\n}\n```\n\n**Step 6: Write tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tests/phase12.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueue } from '../TaskQueue.js';\n\ndescribe('Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown', () => {\n  it('shutdown with no processing tasks completes immediately', async () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const result = await q.shutdown();\n    expect(result.completed).toBe(0);\n    expect(result.forceCancelled).toBe(0);\n    expect(result.durationMs).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(0);\n  });\n\n  it('shutdown prevents new tasks from being added', async () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    await q.shutdown();\n    expect(() => q.add({ payload: 'x' })).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('isShuttingDown returns true after shutdown initiated', async () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const promise = q.shutdown();\n    expect(q.isShuttingDown()).toBe(true);\n    await promise;\n  });\n\n  it('shutdown waits for processing tasks', async () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const t = q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.dequeue();\n\n    // Complete task after a tick\n    setTimeout(() => q.complete(t.id), 20);\n\n    const result = await q.shutdown(1000);\n    expect(t.status).toBe('completed');\n    expect(result.completed).toBe(1);\n    expect(result.forceCancelled).toBe(0);\n  });\n\n  it('shutdown force-cancels after timeout', async () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    q.add({ payload: 'x' });\n    q.dequeue(); // processing but never completed\n\n    const result = await q.shutdown(50); // 50ms timeout\n    expect(result.forceCancelled).toBe(1);\n    expect(result.completed).toBe(0);\n  });\n\n  it('calling shutdown multiple times returns same result', async () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const r1 = await q.shutdown();\n    const r2 = await q.shutdown();\n    expect(r1).toEqual(r2);\n  });\n\n  it('onShutdown callbacks are invoked', async () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const calls: string[] = [];\n    q.onShutdown(() => { calls.push('cb1'); });\n    q.onShutdown(async () => { calls.push('cb2'); });\n    await q.shutdown();\n    expect(calls).toContain('cb1');\n    expect(calls).toContain('cb2');\n  });\n\n  it('shutdown produces duration in result', async () => {\n    const q = new TaskQueue();\n    const result = await q.shutdown();\n    expect(typeof result.durationMs).toBe('number');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 7: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | tail -30\n```\n\n**Step 8: Final build and lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build && npm run lint\n```\n\n**Step 9: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: Phase 12 - graceful shutdown with timeout and force-cancel\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 13: Final Verification\n\n**Files:** none new\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 12\n\n**Step 1: Run all tests**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace && npm test -- --reporter=verbose 2>&1\n```\nExpected: all tests pass across all 12 phases.\n\n**Step 2: Build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\nExpected: no TypeScript errors.\n\n**Step 3: Lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\nExpected: no lint errors.\n\n**Step 4: Review git log**\n\n```bash\ngit log --oneline\n```\n\n**Step 5: Final commit if anything remains unstaged**\n\n```bash\ngit status && git add -A && git diff --staged --stat\n```\n"},"caller":{"type":