+# Task Queue System Implementation Plan
+
+> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.
+
+**Goal:** Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system through 12 incremental phases, exported from `src/index.ts`.
+
+**Architecture:** Single `TaskQueue` class manages all named queues. Each queue has its own pending list (sorted by priority then FIFO), processing set, dead letter queue, middleware stack, and concurrency limit. A pluggable clock function (`() => number`) enables deterministic testing of delays and scheduling.
+
+**Tech Stack:** TypeScript 5.4, Vitest 2.x for tests, ESLint with `@typescript-eslint`, Node16 module resolution, no external runtime dependencies.
